  {
    "ConName": "Under Contract",
    "TimeEntryDate": "2026-03-11",
    "Title": "Re: Library Link",
    "TimeDiff": "- \n0.75 hrs",
    "Notes": "Performed extended troubleshooting on the SharePoint external sharing issue where invited guest users are unable to access the HHCA Collaborative Library folder. Reviewed and tested all Microsoft Entra (Azure AD) external identity configurations, including B2B Collaboration, B2B Direct Connect, Cross-Tenant Access, and Tenant Restrictions, and initially applied corrective changes to enable guest authentication. Verified SharePoint Online organization and site-level external sharing settings, corrected legacy permission issues (including removal of &ldquo;Everyone except external users&rdquo;), and tested fresh guest invitations using &ldquo;Specific People&rdquo; sharing links and clean browser sessions. Despite these adjustments, the guest continued encountering a sign-in error. To rule out configuration conflicts, all previously applied changes were reverted to their original state, and the affected guest account was deleted and recreated to clear any stale authentication or claims data. Additional folder-level and site-level permission checks were performed, along with sign-in log analysis identifying error 500141 during invitation acceptance. After rollback, re-invite, and repeated testing, the issue remains unresolved. A formal Microsoft Support case has been opened for further investigation into potential backend redemption or SharePoint permission inheritance issues.",
    "Resource": "G. Kumar\nCHD-TS1\nSupport - Remote",
    "Requestor": "maritza.a@housingforhealthoc.org",
